      • splitNested

        public void splitNested(eu.cqse.check.framework.scanner.ETokenType openToken,
                        eu.cqse.check.framework.scanner.ETokenType closeToken)
        Splits all streams at the given open and close tokens, e.g. parentheses. The part inside the parentheses will become one new stream and the rest of the original stream as well. In the outside part, the inside part is replaced by the SENTINEL_TOKEN token. For example: a ( b ) c would be split into a ( sentinel ) c and b. Outer parts are guaranteed to be stored before inner parts in the tokenStreams list.
